<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<section class="guide-hero-v35">
  <p class="eyebrow">Buyer Guide</p>
  <h1>How to buy a used wall printer with less risk.</h1>
  <p>Used wall printers can be good opportunities, but condition, printhead health, accessories, software, and logistics must be verified carefully before payment.</p>
</section>

<section class="guide-steps-v35">
  <article>
    <span>1</span>
    <h2>Start with the listing</h2>
    <p>Review price, location, year, brand, model, printhead type, working status, images, and any known defects. Shortlist only machines with enough information to justify a conversation.</p>
  </article>
  <article>
    <span>2</span>
    <h2>Request seller contact</h2>
    <p>Use the contact request form on the machine detail page. After admin review, contact details may be released so you can speak directly with the seller.</p>
  </article>
  <article>
    <span>3</span>
    <h2>Verify before payment</h2>
    <p>Ask for live video, recent photos, nozzle tests, serial number, proof of ownership, accessory list, software status, and a written agreement before sending money.</p>
  </article>
  <article>
    <span>4</span>
    <h2>Plan logistics early</h2>
    <p>Confirm packaging, pickup address, dimensions, weight, export documents, import duties, taxes, insurance, and responsibility for shipping damage.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="guide-cta-v35">
  <div>
    <h2>Need a structured checklist?</h2>
    <p>Use the verification checklist before making a purchase decision.</p>
  </div>
  <a class="btn primary" href="/verification-checklist">Open checklist</a>
</section>
